CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier, October 24, 1959, pg. 2 reads: "Dedicate Homewood YMCA -...At ceremonies Sunday, the new $70,000 brick YMCA branch building, which has been built next to the old frame house, was dedicated.  The YMCA will serve some 10,000 youngsters and young men in the area.  The entire staff welcomes you to visit and participate in the program which has community interest."
TitMainTitle: Exterior of Homewood Brushton Branch YMCA with sign reading "Welcome...Open House Week," Bennett Street, Homewood, another version
